This paper deals with live video streaming over P2P networks, which involves multimedia (cs.MM) and networking (cs.NI) aspects. The paper proposes a new method for optimizing the utilization of peers' outbound bandwidth, which involves modeling and algorithmic design, falling under the categories of distributed computing (cs.DC) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also mentions the use of a maximum flow-based model, which is a well-known concept in information theory (cs.IT).
